<h2><a name='naming'>Naming Conventions:</a></h2>
<set name='name'><em>Agent</em></set>

<p> An Agent name without a final slash is redirected to the Agent's ``home
page'' (usually <code>home.xh</code>).  With a final slash you will always go
to a more-or-less generic index page.  A name of the form <a
href='/&AGENT:name;~'>/&name;~</a> (i.e. appending a tilde to the Agent's
name) will take you to the Agent's ``home page.''  In the 1-line index above,
the generic index is linked from the ``<code>/</code>'' <em>after</em> the
name.

<dl>
  <dt> <a href='/&AGENT:name;'>/&name;</a>
  </dt><dd> Usually, the &name; agent's home page;, except that some agents may
       redirect this (for example, to their data directory).
  </dd><dt> <a href='/&AGENT:name;~'>/&name;~</a>
  </dt><dd> The &name; agent's <em>real</em> home page: <code>home.xh</code>
  in the agent's 
  code directory.  This link works even if the home page is redirected.
  </dd><dt> <a href='/&AGENT:name;~/'>/&name;~/</a>
  </dt><dd> The &name; agent's ``generic'' index page.  Usually not very
       interesting, but occasionally useful if there are things the home page
       leaves out.
  </dd><dt> <a href='/~&AGENT:name;'>/~&name;</a>
  </dt><dd> The home page of the &name; agent's data directory (typically
       <code>index.html</code>), or a generic directory listing.
  </dd><dt> <a href='/~&AGENT:name;/'>/~&name;/</a>
  </dt><dd> A generic listing of the &name; agent's data directory.
</dd></dl>


